  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is contributing to providing appropriate social protection assistance to children infected and affected by EVD and to supporting national efforts to apply proven, evidence-based outbreak and control measures in West Africa.

In collaboration with government and other INGOs, ChildFund will carry out community awareness raising in affected communities in Guinea, Liberia and Sierra Leone. It will provide psychosocial support to affected children in affected communities, support the development of increased community capacity building and resilience for affected children, and put in place mechanisms and systems for improved safety and security. As the number of children separated from their parents through the death of one or both parents, this project will support the efforts of national governments in developing creative ways of responding to the needs of these children. 

The project provides temporary facilities were contact children who as a result of being in contact with their parents who were infected by Ebola will be monitored for 21 days to be cleared of the infection. They will be provided with a safe and secure environment while they are being monitored, and once they are cleared, a family tracing and reunification process will take place to get them safely reunited with their family or a foster parent, as ChildFund firmly believes that the best place for the child is the family.</narrative>
  </description>
